      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BANDIT MIA (2) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (30.11) at Wentworth Park over 520m. Has good speed and a low draw is a big help. One of the contenders. MELLCAT SKA (8) steps out a further 80m to an untried trip. Comes here a last start placegetter at Goulburn in Maiden (25.33). With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. ZIPPING MERRITT (5) was in winning form two back (20.99) at this track but ran below best last time there, finishing 7th. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Expected to give a good account. BEER TIME (4) will run well despite no experience on this track.",
